1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:09,420
ParkIQ — AI-powered parking enforcement intelligence,
built on 115,000 real Bengaluru traffic police records.

2
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:20,888
Bengaluru loses 60 minutes daily per commuter.
Officers are deployed reactively with no visibility into where violations peak.

3
00:00:21,088 --> 00:00:34,480
Two real datasets: 298,450 BTP violation records
and 8,173 ASTRAM traffic incidents — both covering the same 54 police stations.

4
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:44,280
The live heatmap plots 20,000 GPS-verified violation points
across Bengaluru, weighted by vehicle severity from scooter to truck.

5
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:57,128
Top hotspot: Safina Plaza Junction with 5,882 violations.
The top 5 junctions account for 25% of all named-junction violations.

6
00:00:57,328 --> 00:01:08,176
Peak enforcement window: 10 AM IST.
Mondays through Fridays see highest counts. Night drives spike between 2–5 AM.

7
00:01:08,376 --> 00:01:17,328
Cross-correlating with ASTRAM incidents:
stations with active enforcement show fewer traffic events.

8
00:01:17,528 --> 00:01:27,296
10 officers assigned to priority zones across 3 shifts.
4,706 violations addressable per deployment cycle.

9
00:01:27,496 --> 00:01:36,952
Cars are the top offender type.
The vehicle-by-hour heatmap reveals when each type causes the most blockages.

10
00:01:37,152 --> 00:01:47,112
Priority score = 40% frequency
+ 30% peak-hour + 20% incident correlation + 10% severity.

11
00:01:47,312 --> 00:01:57,008
From raw CSV data to deployable patrol schedules —
a complete intelligence pipeline, real-time ready for BTP.

12
00:01:57,208 --> 00:02:08,152
ParkIQ: making Bengaluru's roads smarter, one junction at a time.
Gridlock Hackathon 2.0 · Problem Statement 1.
